 L dwarfs. Finally, we\ndiscuss one peculiar T dwarf, 2MASS 0937+2931, which has very blue\nnear-infrared colors (J-K$_s$ = $-0.89\\pm$0.24) due to suppression of the 2.1\n$\\micron$ peak. The feature is likely caused by enhanced collision-induced\nH$_2$ absorption in a high pressure or low metallicity photosphere.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Aug 2001 17:16:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
